<heading id="D0EB9C7AFFC3FF926BB0FC0AFDFEFC76" bold="true" box="[151,544,964,990]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BB0FC0AFDFEFC76" bold="true" box="[151,544,964,990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926BC9FC0AFDFEFC76" authority="Mayr, 1855" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" box="[238,544,964,990]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BC9FC0AFE53FC76" bold="true" box="[238,397,964,990]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Tetramorium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926AB3FC0AFDFEFC76" author="Mayr, G." box="[404,544,964,990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="273 - 478" refId="ref7787" refString="Mayr, G. (1855) Formicina austriaca. Beschreibung der bisher im osterreichischen Kaiserstaate aufgefundenen Ameisen, nebst Hinzufugung jener in Deutschland, in der Schweiz und in Italien vorkommenden Arten. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch- Botanischen Vereins in Wien, 5, 273 - 478." type="journal article" year="1855">Mayr, 1855</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C306789DFFC3FF926BB0FBC5FAF8FB7F" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC3FF926BB0FBC5FAF8FB7F" blockId="9.[151,1436,1034,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926BB0FBC5FEF6FB8A" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" box="[151,296,1035,1058]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BB0FBC5FEF6FB8A" box="[151,296,1035,1058]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Tetramorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the most diverse ant genera in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF9268B3FBC4FBFEFB8B" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint-Fargeau" authorityYear="1835" box="[916,1056,1034,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Myrmicinae">Myrmicinae</taxonomicName>
, with 518 described taxa (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926E60FBC4FF0CFBEF" author="Bolton, B." pageId="9" pageNumber="574" refId="ref6513" refString="Bolton, B. (1995) A new general catalogue of the ants of the world. Cambridge: Harvard University Press, 504 pp." type="book" year="1995">
<collectingRegion id="49D8E5F4FFC3FF926E60FBC4FA49FB8B" box="[1351,1431,1034,1059]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bolton" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Bolton</collectingRegion>
, 1995
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926BFAFBE0FE6FFBEF" author="Bolton, B. &amp; Alpert, G. &amp; Ward, P. S." box="[221,433,1070,1095]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" refId="ref6540" refString="Bolton, B., Alpert, G. &amp; Ward, P. S. (2007) Bolton's Catalogue of Ants of the World: 1758 - 2005, CD-ROM. Harvard University Press, Cambridge." type="book" year="2007">
<collectingRegion id="49D8E5F4FFC3FF926BFAFBE0FEF4FBEF" box="[221,298,1070,1095]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bolton" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Bolton</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926A17FBE1FEB6FBEF" box="[304,360,1070,1095]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
, 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926A9BFBE0FD95FBEF" author="Bolton, B." box="[444,587,1070,1095]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" refId="ref6579" refString="Bolton, B. (2013) An online catalog of the ants of the World. Version 1 January 2013 Available from: http: // www. antcat. org / catalog / (Accessed 5 May 2013)" type="url" year="2013">
<collectingRegion id="49D8E5F4FFC3FF926A9BFBE0FDD7FBEF" box="[444,521,1070,1095]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bolton" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Bolton</collectingRegion>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
), distributed worldwide in the tropics and temperate regions (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926FDFFBE0FA4EFBEF" author="Brown, W. L., Jr." box="[1272,1424,1070,1095]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" refId="ref6670" refString="Brown, W. L., Jr. (2000) Diversity of ants. In: Agosti, D., Majer, J., Alonso, E. &amp; Schultz, T. R. (Eds) Ants: standard methods for measuring and monitoring biodiversity. Biological diversity hand book series. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington and London, 280 pp." type="book" year="2000">Brown, 2000</bibRefCitation>
). The genus has been comprehensively revised for the majority of the zoogeographic regions (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926F99FB9CFA8EFBC3" author="Bolton, B." box="[1214,1360,1106,1131]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="281 - 379" refId="ref6233" refString="Bolton, B. (1976) The ant tribe Tetramoriini (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Constituent genera, review of smaller genera and revision of Triglyphothrix Forel. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 34, 281 - 379." type="journal article" year="1976">
<collectingRegion id="49D8E5F4FFC3FF926F99FB9CFAD2FBC3" box="[1214,1292,1106,1131]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bolton" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Bolton</collectingRegion>
1976
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926E7AFB9CFA46FBC3" author="Bolton, B." box="[1373,1432,1106,1131]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="67 - 151" refId="ref6280" refString="Bolton, B. (1977) The ant tribe Tetramoriini (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). The genus Tetramorium Mayr in the Oriental and Indo-Australian regions, and in Australia. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 36, 67 - 151." type="journal article" year="1977">1977</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926BB0FBB8FF0CFB27" author="Bolton, B." box="[151,210,1142,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="129 - 181" refId="ref6329" refString="Bolton, B. (1979) The ant tribe Tetramoriini (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). The genus Tetramorium Mayr in the Malagasy region and in the New World. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomolog y, 38, 129 - 181." type="journal article" year="1979">1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926BC5FBB8FEC3FB27" author="Bolton, B." box="[226,285,1142,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="193 - 384" refId="ref6378" refString="Bolton, B. (1980) The ant tribe Tetramoriini (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). The genus Tetramorium Mayr in the Ethiopian zoogeographical region. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Entomology, 40, 193 - 384." type="journal article" year="1980">1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926A0AFBB8FEB6FB27" author="Bolton, B." box="[301,360,1142,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="243 - 248" refId="ref6423" refString="Bolton, B. (1985) The ant genus Triglyphothrix Forel a synonym of Tetramorium Mayr. (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Journal of Natural History, 19, 243 - 248. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938500770191" type="journal article" year="1985">1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926A5FFBB8FD4BFB27" author="Hita Garcia, F. &amp; Fischer, G. &amp; Peters, M. K." box="[376,661,1142,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 90" refId="ref7321" refString="Hita Garcia, F., Fischer, G. &amp; Peters, M. K. (2010) Taxonomy of the Tetramorium weitzeckeri species group (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in the Afrotropical zoogeographical region. Zootaxa, 2704, 1 - 90." type="journal article" year="2010">
Hita Garcia 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF92692CFBB9FD96FB27" box="[523,584,1142,1167]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926981FBB8FC3BFB27" author="Hita Garcia, F. &amp; Fisher, B. L." box="[678,997,1142,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref7367" refString="Hita Garcia, F. &amp; Fisher, B. L. (2011) The ant genus Tetramorium Mayr (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in the Malagasy region - introduction, definition of species groups, and revision of the T. bicarinatum, T. obesum, T. sericeiventre and T. tosii species groups. Zootaxa, 3039, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="2011">Hita Garcia &amp; Fisher 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF9268D2FBB8FBE2FB27" author="Hita Garcia, F. &amp; Fisher, B. L." box="[1013,1084,1142,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 123" refId="ref7434" refString="Hita Garcia, F. &amp; Fisher, B. L. (2012 a) The ant genus Tetramorium Mayr (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in the Malagasy region - taxonomy of the T. bessonii, T. bonibony, T. dysalum, T. marginatum, T. tsingy, and T. weitzeckeri species groups. Zootaxa, 3365, 1 - 123." type="journal article" year="2012">2012a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926F6AFBB8FB49FB27" author="Hita Garcia, F. &amp; Fisher, B. L." box="[1101,1175,1142,1167]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref7503" refString="Hita Garcia, F. &amp; Fisher, B. L. (2012 b) The ant genus Tetramorium Mayr (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in the Malagasy region - taxonomic revision of the T. kelleri and T. tortuosum species groups. Zootaxa, 3592, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2012">2012b</bibRefCitation>
). For many years, the Palaearctic region was lacking revisions but recently several important contributions have been published (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926E6CFB54FEC6FB7F" author="Steiner, F. M. &amp; Schlick-Steiner, B. C. &amp; Sanetra, M. &amp; Ljubomirov, T. &amp; Antonova, V. &amp; Christian, E. &amp; Stauffer, C." pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="23 - 35" refId="ref8691" refString="Steiner, F. M., Schlick-Steiner, B. C., Sanetra, M., Ljubomirov, T., Antonova, V., Christian, E. &amp; Stauffer, C. (2005) Towards DNA aided biogeography: An example from Tetramorium ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Annales Zoologici Fennici, 42, 23 - 35." type="journal article" year="2005">
Steiner 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BB0FB71FF11FB7F" box="[151,207,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
, 2005
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926A03FB70FD86FB7F" author="Schlick-Steiner, B. C. &amp; Steiner, F. M. &amp; Moder, K. &amp; Seifert, B. &amp; Sanetra, M. &amp; Dyreson, E. &amp; Stauffer, C. &amp; Christian, E." box="[292,600,1214,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="259 - 273" refId="ref8192" refString="Schlick-Steiner, B. C., Steiner, F. M., Moder, K., Seifert, B., Sanetra, M., Dyreson, E., Stauffer, C. &amp; Christian, E. (2006) A multidisciplinary approach reveals cryptic diversity in Western Palearctic Tetramorium ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 40, 259 - 273. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2006.03.005" type="journal article" year="2006">
Schlick-Steiner 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926AF0FB71FDD1FB7F" box="[471,527,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926943FB70FCF1FB7F" author="Csosz, S. &amp; Radchenko, A. &amp; Schulz, A." box="[612,815,1214,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6921" refString="Csosz, S., Radchenko, A. &amp; Schulz, A. (2007) Taxonomic revision of the Palaearctic Tetramorium chefketi species complex (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Zootaxa, 1405, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="2007">
Csõsz 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF92698AFB71FD3BFB7F" box="[685,741,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
, 2007
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF92681DFB70FBE8FB7F" author="Csosz, S. &amp; Schulz, A." box="[826,1078,1214,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref6961" refString="Csosz, S. &amp; Schulz, A. (2010) A taxonomic review of the Palaearctic Tetramorium ferox species-complex (Hymenoptera, Formicidae). Zootaxa, 2401, 1 - 29." type="journal article" year="2010">Csõsz &amp; Schulz, 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926F66FB70FAC4FB7F" author="Steiner, F. M. &amp; Seifert, B. &amp; Moder, K. &amp; Schlick-Steiner, B. C." box="[1089,1306,1214,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="223 - 254" refId="ref8758" refString="Steiner, F. M., Seifert, B., Moder, K. &amp; Schlick-Steiner, B. C. (2010) A multisource solution for a complex problem in biodiversity research: Description of the cryptic ant species Tetramorium alpestre sp. n. (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 249, 223 - 254. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2010.09.003" type="journal article" year="2010">
Steiner 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926FB0FB71FB0EFB7F" box="[1175,1232,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">et al.</emphasis>
, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
